 Someday Louisa
Louisa will be 

1067
01:15:42,080 --> 01:15:45,152
 More than just a Fräulein to me 

1068
01:15:45,240 --> 01:15:49,392
 More beer!
More beer! 

1069
01:15:49,480 --> 01:15:53,029
 More beer! 

1070
01:16:08,080 --> 01:16:11,595
Gosh, with all this raw talent around,
why can't us kids get together...

1071
01:16:11,680 --> 01:16:13,079
and put on ourselves a show?

1072
01:16:13,160 --> 01:16:16,789
Maybe we can find ourselves
a barn or something, and maybe...

1073
01:16:20,240 --> 01:16:22,629
I could stand anything but failure.

1074
01:16:24,000 --> 01:16:26,309
- Where's the telephone?
- In there.

1075
01:16:33,520 --> 01:16:35,954
Give me Jeff Cordova's room, please.

1076
01:16:37,080 --> 01:16:40,470
Hello, Jeff. This is Tony.
Now, don't say anything. Just listen.

1077
01:16:40,560 --> 01:16:43,120
I'm here with all the kids,
and we've come to a decision.

1078
01:16:43,200 --> 01:16:46,954
We're not closing this show,
if you can call it a show. We're going on.

1079
01:16:47,040 --> 01:16:50,316
We're going to keep it on the road
and redo it from top to bottom.

1080
01:16:50,400 --> 01:16:52,231
 It won't be a modern version of Faust... 

1081
01:16:52,320 --> 01:16:54,880
 Pilgrim 's Progress, or the Book of Job
in swing time. 

1082
01:16:54,960 --> 01:16:57,599
It'll be our show,
the show we started out to do...

1083
01:16:57,680 --> 01:17:00,240
the book the Martons wrote,
with the songs you threw out.

1084
01:17:00,320 --> 01:17:03,153
It'll have laughs and entertainment.
You remember entertainment?

1085
01:17:03,240 --> 01:17:05,196
Look, we'd love to have you with us, Jeff.

1086
01:17:05,280 --> 01:17:07,350
But if you're not,
it won't make any difference.

1087
01:17:07,440 --> 01:17:08,873
We're going ahead just the same.

1088
01:17:08,960 --> 01:17:11,793
We're going to put this thing across,
aren't we, kids?

1089
01:17:11,880 --> 01:17:14,917
 - All right. What do you say?
- Hello? There's nobody here. 

1090
01:17:15,000 --> 01:17:17,798
This is the chambermaid, but if you want...

1091
01:17:17,880 --> 01:17:21,156
 - I'll leave a message for Mr. Cordova.
- Thank you, madam. 

1092
01:17:21,680 --> 01:17:23,033
He isn't in.

1093
01:17:34,080 --> 01:17:36,389
Jeff, did you hear what I said?

1094
01:17:38,000 --> 01:17:41,276
Tony, I've learned one thing in the theatre,
and it's this:

1095
01:17:41,360 --> 01:17:44,511
one man has to be at the helm,
the rest take orders.

1096
01:17:45,360 --> 01:17:49,035
I believe in what you said.
I got carried away in the wrong direction.

1097
01:17:49,120 --> 01:17:53,671
You've got to be the boss, Tony.
I think you can pull this off brilliantly...

1098
01:17:54,880 --> 01:17:57,110
and I'd like to be a part of it.

1099
01:17:59,120 --> 01:18:00,235
Jeff, you're all right.

1100
01:18:00,320 --> 01:18:02,470
I must tell you one thing.
There isn't any money.

1101
01:18:02,560 --> 01:18:05,711
Colonel Todd and the backers
have stolen away into the night.

1102
01:18:05,800 --> 01:18:06,869
- We've got backers.
- Who?

1103
01:18:06,960 --> 01:18:09,076
A bunch of painters.
A fellow named Degas from...

1104
01:18:09,160 --> 01:18:12,072
- You wouldn't sell your paintings.
- Sure, they love the theatre.

1105
01:18:12,160 --> 01:18:16,073
I figure we need five or six weeks on tour
to do what we have to do with this show.

1106
01:18:16,160 --> 01:18:18,594
- Jeff, would you help us with bookings?
- Of course.

1107
01:18:18,680 --> 01:18:21,877
Hal, have you got paper and pencil?
We can send a telegram.

1108
01:18:24,280 --> 01:18:26,316
- Washington? Washington's open.
- And Boston.

1109
01:18:26,400 --> 01:18:27,435
Boston's very good.

1110
01:18:27,520 --> 01:18:30,671
Can we go to Philadelphia, Detroit,
then come on back to New York?

1111
01:18:30,760 --> 01:18:34,275
- Paul, aren't you excited?
- Yeah. It's wonderful.

1112
01:18:35,280 --> 01:18:37,191
I wish them a lot of luck.

1113
01:18:38,640 --> 01:18:41,837
- This kind of leaves us out.
- Why?

1114
01:18:42,280 --> 01:18:45,397
With Tony doing the dances,
it's not going to be my kind of show.

1115
01:18:45,480 --> 01:18:48,153
Yours, either. I don't want you to do it.

1116
01:18:49,840 --> 01:18:52,070
I wouldn't think of leaving the show, Paul.

1117
01:18:52,160 --> 01:18:56,711
- I've worked too hard on your career to...
- It's my career, and I want to stay.

1118
01:18:58,360 --> 01:19:01,432
I'm taking the 9:00 train
tomorrow morning for New York.

1119
01:19:01,520 --> 01:19:03,431
I expect you to be there.

1120
01:19:05,120 --> 01:19:06,951
Have a nice trip, Paul.

1121
01:19:12,040 --> 01:19:14,554
Dancers, singers, the sketches.

1122
01:19:18,440 --> 01:19:21,591
Listen, kids,
it's going to mean rehearsing every day...

1123
01:19:22,000 --> 01:19:24,070
all day, right up to curtain time.

1124
01:19:24,160 --> 01:19:27,391
We're going to put in new numbers,
and learn them as fast as we can...

1125
01:19:27,480 --> 01:19:30,199
and we're going to yank out all that junk.

1126
01:19:31,480 --> 01:19:34,916
We've got our schedule all worked out,
and it looks pretty good now.

1127
01:19:35,000 --> 01:19:37,992
Philadelphia, Boston, Pittsburgh...

1128
01:19:38,080 --> 01:19:40,310
Washington, Baltimore...

1129
01:19:41,960 --> 01:19:44,474
PHILADELPHIA

1130
01:19:55,560 --> 01:20:00,236
 I see a new sun up in a new sky 

1131
01:20:00,440 --> 01:20:04,877
 And my whole horizon
has reached a new high 

1132
01:20:05,480 --> 01:20:09,951
 Yesterday my heart sang a blue song 

1133
01:20:10,040 --> 01:20:14,750
 But today hear it hum a cheery new song 

1134
01:20:14,840 --> 01:20:19,436
 I dreamed a new dream
I saw a new face 

1135
01:20:19,560 --> 01:20:24,350
 And I'm spreading sunshine
all over the place 

1136
01:20:24,440 --> 01:20:29,150
 With a new point of view
here's what greets my eye 

1137
01:20:29,880 --> 01:20:31,996
 New love 

1138
01:20:32,080 --> 01:20:34,116
 New luck 

1139
01:20:34,200 --> 01:20:38,751
 - New sun
- And there's a new sun 

1140
01:20:38,880 --> 01:20:43,635
 In the sky 

1141
01:20:46,600 --> 01:20:49,068
BOSTON

1142
01:20:52,720 --> 01:20:56,474
 I guess I'll have to change my plan 

1143
01:20:57,480 --> 01:21:01,439
 I should've realized
there'd be another man 

1144
01:21:01,960 --> 01:21:06,112
 I overlooked that point completely 

1145
